Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.57,0:00:12.18,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:15.85,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:21.85,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.85,0:00:36.63,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.73,0:00:43.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.57,0:00:51.35,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.18,0:00:58.76,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:05.86,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.03,0:01:12.50,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.94,0:01:19.14,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.14,0:01:29.12,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:46.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bring news!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:53.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.81,0:01:56.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good news, I trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.38,0:01:58.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:03.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His Highness Prince Chagum\Nhas driven off the evil demons...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:06.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...rendered assistance in\Nthe birth of the water spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.92,0:02:10.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and is returning to the\Npalace at this very moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.43,0:02:16.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He has done well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.83,0:02:21.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall immediately lift the order of\Nsilence and have the entire palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.10,0:02:24.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...begin preparations\Nfor a ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:26.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let it be known far and wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.68,0:02:30.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He is the founding father Torugaru\Nreborn, who, by the grace of heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:33.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...paved the way for the\Ncreation of our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.18,0:02:34.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:40.06,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 26\NDeparture
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.66,0:02:48.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.77,0:02:51.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think the nahji has carried\Nthe egg all the way to the sea by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:02:55.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder when it will\Nbecome a water spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.17,0:02:57.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.17,0:03:00.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if it doesn't start\Nbelching out some clouds soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:02.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the harvest this fall\Nis going to be poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.05,0:03:03.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.55,0:03:12.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Teacher, what\Ndo you suppose Rarunga normally eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.39,0:03:16.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that they go 100 years\Nwithout eating anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.56,0:03:22.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. Even those\Nmonsters are living things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:25.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that they eat other\Ncreatures the rest of the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:29.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and the Nyunga Ro Chaga are\Na treat they only get once a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.34,0:03:34.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see. Even though\Nthey're called egg-eaters...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.58,0:03:37.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...they can't actually eat the eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.75,0:03:43.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anyone besides me\Nthat was implanted with an egg?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.22,0:03:49.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, there was a bear cub.\NWe saw it get eaten by a Rarunga.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.10,0:03:54.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.08,0:04:08.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like us to do, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:13.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The prince seldom leaves\Nthe spear-wielder's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.68,0:04:17.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, female bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.12,0:04:19.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.66,0:04:24.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga, even if you were\Nso ordered by the mikado...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.39,0:04:26.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...surely it is no longer necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:30.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,None of us wish to cause\NHis Highness more grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:35.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should feel that desire\Nmore keenly than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.75,0:04:46.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are right. I was\Nabout to do the wrong thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.92,0:04:49.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall discuss this with the mikado.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:53.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mon, Jin, thank you.\NYou have my gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.12,0:05:32.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, go ride in the palanquin.\NThey look embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.50,0:05:33.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.63,0:05:38.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't feel right to ride in the\Npalanquin when you're hurt, Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.77,0:05:40.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate the sentiment, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:44.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, let him have his way.\NChagum says he doesn't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.31,0:05:48.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. And besides,\Nwe're almost at Kosenkyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:14.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.00,0:06:18.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you start off by letting\Nyour mother see that you're safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.68,0:06:31.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have made arrangements\Nfor you within the palace as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.19,0:06:34.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please relax and enjoy\Nyourselves until you are sent for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:39.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I like the sound of that. Why don't\Nwe have ourselves a grand time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.13,0:06:42.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will look after your spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.32,0:07:03.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.42,0:07:06.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.22,0:07:08.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.80,0:07:13.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:17.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum...I always believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.83,0:07:21.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always believed that you were\Nstill alive somewhere out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:30.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at how you have grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.48,0:07:34.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thanks to Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:37.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, what became of that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:39.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She came back with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.42,0:07:42.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is probably somewhere\Nwith Shuga in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.09,0:07:45.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.02,0:08:11.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Sagum, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.24,0:08:29.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This bath hits the spot...\NDoesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.41,0:08:33.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NYou look awfully pensive over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.81,0:08:39.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. It's finally starting\Nto hit home that it's really over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.39,0:08:47.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.29,0:08:50.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. I still have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.39,0:08:53.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Set out on another journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:55.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't given that\Nany thought either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.74,0:09:04.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, there's talk of\Narranging a bride for Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.71,0:09:08.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to the health\Nsprings over the winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.18,0:09:11.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...an old acquaintance of mine\Nkept pestering me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:12.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She says her daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:16.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...saw Tanda brewing medicine\Nfor a retired old geezer there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:18.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and fell head over heels for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.19,0:09:24.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like me, she's quite a looker.\NShe has a fine disposition too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:27.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They sound like a fine match.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.80,0:09:38.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For heaven's sake...\NI can't possibly eat all this food.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.14,0:09:42.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I'll start with the food\Nthat looks like it will go bad first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.08,0:09:43.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:47.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so stingy. Start with\Nwhatever you want to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.28,0:09:51.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher, don't you think\Nyou've had too much to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:52.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who asked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.32,0:09:55.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I plan to drink every last drop\Nof liquor they have in the palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.99,0:09:58.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Bring me more sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.60,0:10:01.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:07.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's no wonder that a simple\Nbowl of porridge seemed new to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:09.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...if he was served\Nfeasts like this every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.77,0:10:11.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.24,0:10:13.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.25,0:10:23.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry!\NWe'll see Chagum soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.35,0:10:27.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That couldn't possibly have been\Nthe last time we'd ever see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.36,0:10:30.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm sure that Chagum\Nis just as eager to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.86,0:10:35.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:42.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.14,0:10:52.15,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.86,0:11:03.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Approach me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:13.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.35,0:11:32.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is good that you have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.06,0:11:34.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.76,0:11:37.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga has informed me of\Nwhat transpired on your journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.83,0:11:42.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been long and difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.27,0:11:46.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, it was one\Nworthy of a child of heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.44,0:11:48.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Truly a great deed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.21,0:11:55.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was only through the assistance of\Na great many people that I succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.11,0:11:57.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Especially that of Balsa, who--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.58,0:11:59.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Especially that of Balsa, who--\NForget you ever met that woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.78,0:12:03.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the common masses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.85,0:12:07.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...you are the hero who saved\Nthe country in her time of crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.16,0:12:11.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For a country, as well as for\Nall those who reside in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:15.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...having a hero is the\Ngreatest possible honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.03,0:12:19.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One which no amount\Nof money can buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:22.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are a treasure\Nbestowed upon us by heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.37,0:12:30.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am given to understand that this Kanbal\Nwoman is a most capable individual...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.05,0:12:34.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...one who protected you with no\Nthought of reward or her own safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.62,0:12:39.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely she would have no\Nobjections to you being our hero...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.62,0:12:42.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and guiding the\NShin-Yogo empire into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.57,0:12:54.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.94,0:12:57.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Live as our hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.08,0:13:05.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With Sagum now gone,\Nyour role is now to live as a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.12,0:13:09.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For both you, who has made\Nan ally of the water spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.18,0:13:14.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...as well as for Shin-Yogo,\Nthe road ahead is a bright one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.54,0:13:29.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga, what is Balsa doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.04,0:13:32.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is resting in the\Nguest quarters, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.74,0:13:34.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.21,0:13:38.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please understand,\NYour Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.51,0:13:44.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The moment you returned here,\Nyou became the crown prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:49.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Arrangements have been\Nmade for them to receive...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.46,0:13:53.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a more than suitable reward\Nbefore the ceremony tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.50,0:14:01.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa must have known\Nthat this would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.00,0:14:03.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is why she\Ntold me about Jiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:23.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long are these people\Ngoing to keep us waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.15,0:14:52.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.52,0:14:53.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.86,0:14:56.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't kidding when they\Nsaid that the clothes make the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.49,0:14:57.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.46,0:14:59.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, they can't hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:09.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In light of your service to His Highness\Nthe crown prince, child of heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.77,0:15:12.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...His Majesty the mikado\Nshall now reward you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.78,0:15:22.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You there, step forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.66,0:15:36.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:03.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.77,0:16:12.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.80,0:16:17.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's too much trouble!\NGo up there and fetch mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.28,0:16:26.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather talk to Chagum one more\Ntime than receive something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:30.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll take your\Nshare off your hands later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.12,0:16:32.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You and your jokes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.53,0:16:46.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Halt! Commoners are not allowed\Nto pass through this gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:48.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go down the path to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.20,0:16:50.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.74,0:16:53.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That path is more suitable\Nfor the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:55.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I think you're\Ntaking this a little too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.08,0:16:57.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.98,0:17:02.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose we should\Ndo as they say for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.57,0:17:17.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.94,0:17:23.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:32.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L...I don't want to be\Nthe crown prince!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.41,0:17:35.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to keep traveling\Nwith you forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.62,0:17:37.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to leave you, Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.78,0:18:11.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, do you want\Nto run away with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.76,0:18:25.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Would you like me\Nto cause a commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.86,0:18:53.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to cause a commotion.\NYou can save it for some other child.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.77,0:19:01.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And maybe that child\Nwill be yours and Tanda's!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.27,0:19:09.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good one! Well said!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.18,0:19:12.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've learned to\Nspeak your mind, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.39,0:19:22.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.36,0:19:24.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:43.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.72,0:19:50.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to call me Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.69,0:19:53.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to say,\N"Goodbye, Chagum."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:01.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Goodbye, Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.27,0:20:09.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:13.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda, Torogai, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.10,0:20:38.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Torogai will be\Nstaying at the hut for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.03,0:20:39.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.90,0:20:45.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could've talked\Nto Chagum again too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.84,0:20:49.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who's to say that you\Nwon't see him again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.21,0:20:51.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:59.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I wonder why Balsa decided\Nto go back to Kanbal all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.76,0:21:01.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.99,0:21:05.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that Chagum was\Nsupposed to be her eighth soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.59,0:21:08.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was going to\Nsettle down after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.73,0:21:15.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's one other person\Nthat only Balsa can put to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.24,0:21:21.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I just hope she doesn't keep you\Nwaiting another two years this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:26.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If she does, I'll deal with it.\NI'll still be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.31,0:21:29.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, there's such a\Nthing as too much patience...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:39.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.27,0:21:49.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Tanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.34,0:21:54.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A cloud!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.56,0:22:44.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should have had some of Tanda's\Nwild vegetable stew before I left.

Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.81,0:23:10.15,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.15,0:23:17.29,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:22.56,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.56,0:23:29.91,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.91,0:23:44.19,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.19,0:23:53.56,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.56,0:24:00.34,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.34,0:24:05.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.47,0:24:13.85,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.85,0:24:18.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.05,0:24:26.29,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.29,0:24:36.60,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
